{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d6cf7531-3c33-4e30-9215-3a3692a401be","content":"Replace the `VSTest@3` task with `DotNetCoreCLI@2` (or a plain `dotnet test` script step). Microsoft.Testing.Platform runs tests via `dotnet test` and supports TRX + coverage natively through command-line switches.\n\n**Before (VSTest@3):**\n```yaml\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**/*Tests.dll'\n    resultsFolder: $(Build.ArtifactStagingDirectory)/TestResults\n```\n\n**After (dotnet test):**\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run Tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration Release\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Build.ArtifactStagingDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish Test Results'\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '**/*.trx'\n    searchFolder: $(Build.ArtifactStagingDirectory)/TestResults\n  condition: always()\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish Code Coverage'\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Build.ArtifactStagingDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n  condition: always()\n```\n\n**Key changes:**\n\n1. **`--logger \"trx\"`** — produces `.trx` files (same format VSTest used).\n2. **`--collect \"Code Coverage\"`** — collects coverage via the built-in data collector. For Cobertura XML (needed by `PublishCodeCoverageResults@2`), add the `coverlet.collector` NuGet package and use `--collect \"XPlat Code Coverage\"` instead.\n3. **`PublishTestResults@2`** — still needed to surface results in the Azure DevOps UI; `DotNetCoreCLI@2` can auto-publish, but explicit control is more reliable.\n4. **`condition: always()`** — ensures results publish even when tests fail.\n\nMake sure your test projects reference **MSTest 3.x+** with `<EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>` in the `.csproj` (or `Directory.Build.props`) to opt into Microsoft.Testing.Platform.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9acce1d0-9166-4510-8015-4a3965e31e84","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The repository doesn't have existing pipeline files or relevant documentation. This is a general guidance question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps CI pipelines. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":677,"requestId":"1BDA:BB4CA:20D9E85:243AF61:6A03CE72"},"id":"269d09f5-12d4-4719-ac7c-4fde09182e0c","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:06:07.410Z","parentId":"4af6c49e-13d8-447e-a8fe-3091c8784dbb"}
